Bug Hunter Scenario: You encounter the following Spring `@Service` bean. Users report that when `updateInventory` fails with a `RuntimeException`, the database changes made in `updateStockCount` are NOT rolled back, even though the method is marked as `@Transactional`.

java
@Service
public class InventoryService {

    public void updateInventory(Long id, int quantity) {
        // Business logic
        updateStockCount(id, quantity);
    }

    @Transactional
    public void updateStockCount(Long id, int quantity) {
        // Database update logic
        if (quantity < 0) throw new RuntimeException("Invalid quantity");
    }
}
